&lt;h2&gt;Build the backbone that helps Value Engineering scale across Coveo&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How do you help a growing function scale its impact without losing consistency, quality, or speed? As our Senior Advisor of Value Engineering Operations, you will build the systems, standards, and workflows that help Coveo’s Value Engineering function operate more effectively and scale more consistently across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is primarily focused on creating the operational backbone behind the function - from shared tools and templates to governance, knowledge flows, and automation. At the same time, you will help extend the impact of Value Engineering across Coveo by improving adoption of self-serve value tools, turning field insight into reusable guidance, and helping teams stay aligned on how Coveo creates value as products and priorities evolve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;As our Senior Advisor of Value Engineering Operations, you will:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the shared tools, templates, and repositories that support Value Engineering work across the team and the wider organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish governance for templates, automations, and shared assets so they remain current, trusted, and easy to adopt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption and effective use of Coveo Lift (Value Engineering Platform) and other self-serve value tools across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build repeatable workflows to capture insights from Business Architecture, Value Engineering, and Transformation and turn them into recurring digests, shared resources, and reusable guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate major product, launch, and strategic developments into clear value guidance and enablement for teams across Coveo.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and launch priority automation and AI-enabled workflows that reduce manual work and improve how value knowledge is captured, maintained, and scaled.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Here is what will qualify you for the role:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in operations, enablement, consulting operations, program management, knowledge management, or similar roles focused on scaling team effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of building repeatable processes, shared systems, or operating models that improve consistency and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong program management and execution skills, with the ability to run multiple initiatives and keep shared systems reliable and up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, with the ability to turn team input into clear standards, documentation, and reusable resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What will make you stand out:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in or supporting consulting, value engineering, pre-sales, or other customer-facing strategic teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with automation tooling, AI-assisted workflows, or process improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
