&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape the systems behind a world-class employee experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How do you scale people operations thoughtfully when your company is growing, but still values agility? At Coveo, we’re looking for someone who can bridge People, systems, and execution to help us evolve the way our HR technology ecosystem supports the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of People Operations, project management, and enterprise systems. You’ll partner closely with People leaders, Information Systems &amp;amp; Technologies, and executive stakeholders to translate HR needs into scalable solutions across platforms like Workday and our applicant tracking systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As our Senior Enterprise Systems &amp;amp; HRIS Advisor you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate processes, identify optimization opportunities, and recommend scalable solutions adapted to Coveo’s reality and growth stage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive cross-functional HR systems initiatives, from discovery and prioritization to delivery and adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with People teams to translate operational and strategic needs into clear system requirements and implementation plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the main bridge between HR and IS, ensuring priorities, timelines, and tradeoffs stay aligned with business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the evolution of Coveo’s HR technology ecosystem, including Workday and talent acquisition platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with senior stakeholders, including the Chief People Officer and Systems leaders, to influence roadmap decisions and improve employee experience through technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here is what will qualify you for the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience leading HR systems and technology projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of enterprise Human Capital Management (HCM) and/or ERP platforms such as Workday, without necessarily being deeply configuration-focused.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to navigate complex stakeholder environments and translate business needs into actionable technical deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid project management skills, including prioritization, estimation, risk management, and cross-functional coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will make you stand out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in consulting, transformation, or implementation environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to HR technology ecosystems beyond HCMs, such as performance management or applicant tracking systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience scaling processes and systems in mid-sized organizations balancing enterprise ambitions with pragmatic execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business acumen and the ability to challenge ideas constructively while building trust across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you think you can bring this role to life? Send us your application, we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join the Coveolife!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage all qualified candidates to apply regardless of, for example, age, gender, disability, gaps in CV, national or ethnic background.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job description was written by humans, assisted by AI. We may leverage technology in our hiring process to help us see the person behind the resume.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coveo is committed to providing accessible employment practices. If you require accommodation due to a disability at any point during the recruitment process, please contact HR@Coveo.com to discuss your needs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the teams that power our go-to-market success!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What if your hiring strategy directly shaped how the world’s leading brands discover, buy, and grow with Coveo? At Coveo, building high-performing go-to-market teams is central to our growth strategy. Our global expansion is fueled by the talent acquisition partners who attract and hire the people behind our revenue engine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with GTM executive leaders, acting as a strategic partner to design, attract, and scale teams across Sales, Marketing, Customer Experience and Partnerships. Choosing Coveo means helping shape the talent strategy behind an AI-powered platform trusted by some of the world’s most recognized brands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As one of our Senior GTM Talent Partner, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own and drive end-to-end recruitment strategies across our go-to-market functions, aligning hiring priorities with Coveo’s growth objectives and revenue strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Act as a strategic talent partner to GTM executive leaders and senior managers, contributing to strategic hiring discussions and advising on talent strategy, market conditions, and scalable team design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design and execute inclusive, high-quality recruitment processes across North America and Europe, from crafting compelling job descriptions to structuring fair, competency-based interviews, while ensuring rigorous documentation and data integrity within our applicant tracking system (ATS) and related tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build and refine long-term talent attraction strategies, proactively identifying target talent pools and strengthening Coveo’s positioning to consistently attract and engage top-performing GTM profiles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leverage recruitment data, market intelligence, and industry trends to continuously refine sourcing, interviewing, and evaluation approaches to elevate hiring quality and predictability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Represent Coveo in targeted talent attraction initiatives, industry events, and community engagements (including occasional evenings or weekends), reinforcing our presence within key GTM talent ecosystems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here is what will qualify you for the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5+ years of experience in talent acquisition, with a strong focus on go-to-market recruitment (Sales, Marketing, Customer Experience, Partnerships) within complex, fast-growing organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Demonstrated experience partnering with senior GTM leaders and influencing strategic hiring decisions through data-driven insights and market expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven ability to design and execute end-to-end recruitment strategies across multiple regions, including proactive sourcing and structured, competency-based interviewing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong understanding of GTM talent markets, including revenue-generating and customer-facing roles, with the ability to engage highly competitive profiles with credibility and depth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will make you stand out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong business acumen and understanding of revenue models, pipeline generation, and customer lifecycle dynamics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience supporting high-growth or scaling GTM organizations within the technology (ideally SaaS) space across North America and Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Track record of building proactive talent pipelines in competitive, performance-driven markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
